<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-03-17T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-03-17T11:00:00-05:00" n="26" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d26">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/1599</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PTN1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-17T17:00:00+01:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 17, 1915, 5 p. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 7 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>216. British Ambassador not apprehensive Austria and Italy will come to
                            terms. This also my opinion. Things seem smoothing down. Italy prepared,
                            tested new siege guns yesterday, but many think no hostile move will
                            occur before end April. Personally I think likely if she moves it will
                            be without much warning.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_PTN1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson Page</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>